Sneaking off to be a hero

###Sneaking off to be a hero

"Please show me your ID card. Here is a registration form. Please fill it out. "

Zhang Yewen's voice has some hoarse, but this paragraph has been familiar to the heart. On January 31, Zhejiang Provincial Medical Insurance Bureau issued an emergency notice, during the epidemic prevention and control period, retail pharmacies to buy fever, cough medicine staff are required to register the information report. Zhang Yewen is the store manager of a retail pharmacy in Hangzhou. During the Chinese New Year, the store clerk returned to his hometown. As the store manager, he had to cover the shift. Apart from the time when the company picked up the goods, he basically stayed in the store every day and met some customers who came to buy medicine, the above dialogue will appear. If it is a customer who buys a little heat-clearing medicine, Zhang Yewen and his colleagues will also need to measure the guest's body temperature. If there is any abnormal body temperature, then they will find out whether the situation is coming from the "epidemic area" , "If the company tells you to call the police, call the police. ".

"Fortunately, we have not encountered this aspect of the matter" , has been working for nearly half a month of Zhang ye-wen slightly fluke.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Didn't the state say there was? Why don't you have any? I'M GOING TO FILE A COMPLAINT! "

The pharmacy was carrying too much emotion under the influence of the epidemic.

Tan Yong, a 27-year-old local pharmacist from Hangzhou, volunteered to work at Zhang's shop during the Lunar New Year holiday. When the door opened on the morning of February 1, the Shuanghuanglian on the shelf was snatched up by some people waiting outside early. In the afternoon, some people came to ask for masks and Shuanghuanglian. They could only leave with a sense of loss. There are more emotional customers, shouting at Tan Yong, Tan Yong in addition to explain again and again out of stock reasons, there is no other way, very helpless.

When people were first diagnosed in Hangzhou, residents were panic-stricken. Masks and disinfectant were quickly snapped up. Zhang's shop, where they worked, was also out of stock for two or three days. The shop assistants, who had bad tone and physical conflicts, were sometimes scolded by customers, laughing and crying, "did you hide your masks, ready to raise the price? " The experienced pharmacist was fine, some shop assistants are just graduated from the little girl, busy work, psychological pressure is also very big, meet such customers, suffered a lot of grievances.

Not long ago, Tan Yong in a pharmacy in Hubei Students confirmed, he did not dare to tell parents this news, but in the work group to remind colleagues to strengthen protection.

In Special Times, transportation is not convenient, going to the hospital to see a doctor may mean danger, the existence of pharmacies is especially important, there are always people for some specific drugs, walking around the city's pharmacies, store manager Zhang yewen is still persevering, Tan Yong also wants to stay.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Try not to say, try not to say bad, try to say good. "

After Zhang Yewen arrived home, his wife was obviously a little anxious.

"You say if the infected people go to you there to buy medicine! " His wife asked Zhang Yewen do not know how to answer, he can only say with a smile, no, nothing today. "Not afraid of ten thousand, just in case... " , Zhang Yewen silently into the bathroom, wash hands, change clothes, disinfection, he really do not want to let his wife worry.

Every day when he came home from work, Tan Yong's parents would ask him about the store. Did he meet anyone with a cough and fever? "Basically, people in the store would be asked when they came home. We generally said, not much, AH. " Tan Yong has been avoiding talking to his parents about too much work, because they will find flaws, or worry about it in the end.

"Try to say yes, so many people are worried, it is better to worry about their own" , Zhang Yewen they work during this Spring Festival, are very tacitly practice this method.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This special Spring Festival in 2020, in the shadow of the new coronavirus pneumonia, the city's rhythm has been disrupted, there is panic, there is anger, there is helplessness, there is disappointment, but in panic, there is still warmth. Behind the grand narrative of the national rescue, all around us, a group of people from the drug store were on the front line, the doctors were on the front line, they were on the defensive, they were highly strung, physically and mentally exhausted, they were just ordinary people, in a world of silence, with open arms, no one is willing to risk their lives to make money, but the choice to live in silence to become a hero, to protect the health of one side of the people.

2
That never closes

2

###That never closes

It may have never occurred to the drugstore owner that it would be a laudable thing to persist in daily business, but it is so at the moment. Looking down the street, the shop doors are mostly closed, and the drugstore is probably one of the few places of business that still provides services to the residents, even in Wuhan, the worst affected city, there are still 4,084 open pharmacies, accounting for 85 percent of the daily supply.

With the advantage of community network coverage, retail pharmacies have played an important role in early detection of the epidemic, and become an important position in addition to hospitals in the fight against the epidemic. At the beginning of February, the authorities in many places launched an intensive policy on real-name authentication and reporting of sales of antipyretic and cough medicine in retail pharmacies. Citizens are required to register with their real names and fill in information at pharmacies when purchasing related medicines, pharmacy staff will also take the temperature of the customers into the store, abnormal temperature of the customers, urge and persuade them to medical institutions in time, as soon as a high suspicion of infection reported immediately.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
These basic work, to ensure that the epidemic does not spread out of a solid barrier, to combat the epidemic set up an important checkpoint. As the director of the Zhejiang Provincial Bureau of food and Drug Administration said, more than 20,000 pharmacies in Zhejiang Province are more than 20,000 outposts. Every additional screening will add a layer of safety net.

The actions of the people of the drugstores in Zhejiang Province are a microcosm of all their silent and dedicated counterparts in the drugstores all over China. The outbreak was so severe and spread so rapidly that all of China was in a situation of medical shortages. The medical institutions in the front line of the fight against the epidemic frequently rescued, and the emergency supplies touched the hearts of all people. At this moment, the people in the drugstores were unwilling to lag behind, and were within their reach, the whole industry raises the material to send to the epidemic area, contributes the solid strength for the epidemic. The big chain raised supplies and supported the front line. Some small chain and single-unit pharmacies, though their capacity was limited, also increased their manpower, persisted in 24/7 and delivered medicines to their homes within 30 minutes, and launched the service of "delivering medicines to their homes at ease" , which became an outpost that never closed, to ensure the daily use of medicines by the masses in all directions.

To the million sentinels

###To the million sentinels

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In response to the sacrifices and sacrifices made by the people of the apothecary during the anti-epidemic campaign, kANBE golden flute launched a public welfare action, which called for the medical industry and the whole society to pay attention to and respect the people of the pharmacy, by providing insurance coverage for the representatives of the pharmacies on duty during the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic, the hope is that it will appeal to more pharmaceutical and distribution enterprises to join the ranks of the caring drugstores and give back support to the millions of sentinels, cheer for Your Comrades.

"containment is a people's war. Hospitals are the line of fire, our pharmaceutical companies are the arsenal, pharmacies are the checkpoints, and millions of employees are the sentries. We are all comrades-in-arms on the same front. It is our common mission and responsibility to guard our health and win the battle of epidemic prevention and control,"said Hu Jiqiang, president of the China Association of over-the-counter Drugs and Chairman of the Kangenbei Group, "Hope the whole industry to act together, pharmacies to guard the front line, we watch over you. ".

Drugstore people don't back down

4

###Drugstore people don't back down

In the summer of 2019, Tan Yong watched a chinese-made ancient costume drama. He liked one of the scenes very much. He took retreating as a tactic for the down-and-out children. At a time when the lives of his colleagues were in doubt and the lives of the people in the city were at stake, bellowing out "no retreat" with a roaring drum above the Belvedere. He was never a hero, but in that moment, he made a choice with his conscience.

The fight against the epidemic continues. Despite the heavy workload and the risk of infection, more pharmacies are open 24 hours a day and, with today's commitment and responsibility, choose to stay on duty and never back down.
